caption.text:
READ THE CAPTION! ⬇️ Full answers:

1️⃣ "How much do you post per week?" 14-20 feed posts.
I post about 2-3 feed posts per day. In short: The more you post, the more you grow!

2️⃣ "How many Stories do you post per week?" 3-4 Stories PER WEEK.
Less Stories = more views!
If you want ideas for selling on IG Stories, comment STORY on this Reel!

3️⃣ "Do you batch your content?"
ABSOLUTELY!! It's the only way I'm able to post as much as I am without going crazy.

4️⃣ "How often do you talk about what you sell?"
When I'm not in a launch, I average 4-5 promo's per week (usually to a free lead magnet).

This means about 20%-35% of my posts are "selling" or talking about what I offer!

Which answer surprised you the most??

caption.text:
Anyone else ever been there or just me? 😂😂 HOW TO USE THIS AUDIO ⤵️

This audio is blowing up on the app that rhymes with blick block, and is soooo easy to use!

While “trending audios” aren’t a strategy, nor does using them guarantee views…

they CAN BE a great way to come up with EASY post ideas!!

⭐️ For this one, it’s all about not fitting in! ⭐️

Here are some ideas: 💡
• Me at my first Pilates class
• How I sound to my kids when they watch my Reels
• Me trying to talk to the other soccer moms
• POV: I’m trying to fit in with my Gen-Z coworkers
• Trying to sell a house to anyone under the age of 30

If you want 5 trending audio ideas for FREE every week, comment TREND on this Reel 🔥

caption.text:
STOP making new posts EVERY DAY! Here’s the problem: ⤵️

Creating every day means you have no freedom! You’re forced to make a new post every day…

This hamster-wheel leads to BURNOUT!!

Instead: MAKE POSTS IN ADVANCE AND USE @metricoolapp TO SCHEDULE THEM!!

Scheduling your posts will NOT hurt their views or engagement,

But it WILL give you the freedom to run your business & live your life!

⭐️ Comment COOL and I’ll send you the link to try it for free!! 🎉🎉🎉
